# Finalize a freshly cloned AppleFactory template

If this is a freshly cloned AppleFactory template (signals: `Scripts/rename.sh` exists **and**
`Sources/AppTemplate/` still exists, or `Resources/Info.plist` still contains
`com.example.AppTemplate`), follow the canonical workflow in
**[`docs/FINALIZE.md`](docs/FINALIZE.md)** to rebrand it into a real app.

Summary of the workflow (full details, question options, and tables in `docs/FINALIZE.md`):

1. **Ask** the user: app name, bundle ID prefix, one-line description, App Store category,
   distribution (Direct vs App Store), permissions needed, copyright holder, GitHub `owner/repo`,
   and whether to keep the sample code.
2. **Run** `Scripts/rename.sh "<App name>" "<Bundle ID prefix>"` then
   `Scripts/finalize.sh --app "<App name>" --repo "<owner/repo>" --category "<category>"
   [--copyright "<holder>"] [--distribution direct|appstore]`.
3. **Edit** the README description, AGENTS.md project summary, `Resources/Info.plist`
   (`NS*UsageDescription` keys), `Resources/Entitlements.plist` (matching entitlements, no XML
   comments), and PRIVACY/SECURITY as needed.
4. **Verify** with `swift build && swift test`.
5. **Hand off**: suggest `git add -A && git commit`.

Do not run this if `Sources/AppTemplate/` has already been renamed away — the template is already
finalized.
